  <content type="columns">
    <header>JDeveloper Ant Addin Features</header>

    <column>
      <html>
        <h2>IDE Integration</h2>
        <p align="center">
          <img src="images/feature-ide-integ.png" alt="IDE Integration" />
        </p>
        <h3>Ant Buildfile Category In Navigator</h3>
        <table width="100%">
          <tr>
            <td>
              <img src="images/nav-feature.png" alt="Navigator Integration" />
            </td>
            <td valign="top">
          Ant buildfiles in a JDeveloper project are displayed in a special
          category under the project node in the navigator. Buildfiles also
          have their own special icon so they can be easily distinguished
          from other .xml files in your project.
            </td>
          </tr>
        
        </table>

        <h3>Full Integration with JDeveloper's XML Editor</h3>
        
        <table width="100%">
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">
              Ant files can be edited and viewed in JDeveloper's XML
              editor, which offers full syntax highlighting and many other
              powerful features.
            </td>
            <td>
              <img src="images/xml-edit-feature.png" alt="XML Editor" />
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
       
        <h2>Buildfile Generation Wizard</h2>
        <p align="center">
          <img src="images/feature-wizard.png" alt="Buildfile Wizard" />
        </p>
        
        <p>
          You can easily create new Ant buildfiles from existing JDeveloper
          projects using the Buildfile wizard. This wizard will take you
          through the steps of creating your buildfile, allowing you to
          choose and customize the default targets which will be generated. 
        </p>

      </html>
    </column>

    
    <column width="15%">
      <box title="Ant Addin">
        <xsql:include-xsql href="antnav.xml" />
      </box>
    </column>
    
    
